etymologies: late 19th century; earliest use found in Dixon Kemp (1839–1899). From rocker + -ed

definitions: Of the keel of a boat: curving upwards at each end. Also (of a boat): having a keel of this kind.
Of an ice skate: having a blade which curves upwards at each end. Also (of a roller skate): having the wheels arranged in a similar, curved shape.
Of a surfboard: curving upwards at the nose and tail.
